ForAndreea Gabriela Tudor, nature becomes a theatre of memory, inevitably marked by human presence and by the subjective significations attached to it. At the opposite pole,Raluca Spătaru Iancu’spainting seeks to preserve the spontaneous, immediate feeling before the motif, as if the objects of contemplation were being encountered for the very first time, as if the labour of representation were to begin, each time, from a zero point of absolute ingenuousness.Sorin Scurtulescu’sflowers reveal themselves to the gaze in their paradisiacal, luxuriant splendour, whose expression is decisively linked to the nature of the pictorial material, to luminosity and preciousness. Inclined toward synthesis,Ciprian Bodeacarries out a progressive schematization of the “architecture” of iris flowers, from which he extracts an autonomous structure endowed with its own expressive and ordering valences, positioned at the threshold between the descriptive and the non-representational. Each proposition offers an opportunity to expand the realm of experience, a lived discovery under the arc of the joy of seeing and of painting.

Andreea Gabriela Tudor (b. 2001, Brăila), Raluca Spătaru Iancu (b. 1977, Brăila), Sorin Scurtulescu (b. 1979, Timișoara), and Ciprian Bodea (b. 1979, Cugir)are among the most renowned contemporary Romanian artists, authors of numerous exhibitions hosted in museums, galleries, and cultural institutions in Romania and abroad.

Sorin Scurtulescu and Ciprian Bodeaare founding members of one of the most relevant and influential artistic groups active on the current visual arts scene:Grupul Noima.', 'The exhibition’s theme is the centrality of vision—understood both in its common sense of visual perception and in its more specific meaning of attention and discernment—for the act of painting and for the life of the spirit alike. Though far from new, the theme is nevertheless inexhaustible. It is continually renewed and diversified in conjunction with the sensibility of each of the four artists, while simultaneously offering a ground for encounter and dialogue. The exhibition presents four distinct perspectives on nature, four different ways of apprehending and interpreting the material reality of the world.

ForAndreea Gabriela Tudor, nature becomes a theatre of memory, inevitably marked by human presence and by the subjective significations attached to it. At the opposite pole,Raluca Spătaru Iancu’spainting seeks to preserve the spontaneous, immediate feeling before the motif, as if the objects of contemplation were being encountered for the very first time, as if the labour of representation were to begin, each time, from a zero point of absolute ingenuousness.Sorin Scurtulescu’sflowers reveal themselves to the gaze in their paradisiacal, luxuriant splendour, whose expression is decisively linked to the nature of the pictorial material, to luminosity and preciousness. Inclined toward synthesis,Ciprian Bodeacarries out a progressive schematization of the “architecture” of iris flowers, from which he extracts an autonomous structure endowed with its own expressive and ordering valences, positioned at the threshold between the descriptive and the non-representational. Each proposition offers an opportunity to expand the realm of experience, a lived discovery under the arc of the joy of seeing and of painting.

Andreea Gabriela Tudor (b. 2001, Brăila), Raluca Spătaru Iancu (b. 1977, Brăila), Sorin Scurtulescu (b. 1979, Timișoara), and Ciprian Bodea (b. 1979, Cugir)are among the most renowned contemporary Romanian artists, authors of numerous exhibitions hosted in museums, galleries, and cultural institutions in Romania and abroad.

Sorin Scurtulescu and Ciprian Bodeaare founding members of one of the most relevant and influential artistic groups active on the current visual arts scene:Grupul Noima.', null, null, '04-26.10.2025, “Gheorghe Naum” Gallery, Brăila Museum “Carol I”, Brăila, Romania', '04-26.10.2025, “Gheorghe Naum” Gallery, Brăila Museum “Carol I”, Brăila, Romania', 'https://rptwowkkejecvvbfsgkt.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/artwork-images/wp-import/exhibitions/the-gift-of-vision/6.-installation-view_darul-vederii_muzeul-brailei_2025.jpg', true, 4) on conflict (slug) do update set title_en=excluded.title_en, title_ro=excluded.title_ro, subtitle_en=excluded.subtitle_en, poster_url=excluded.poster_url, venue_en=excluded.venue_en, start_date=excluded.start_date, end_date=excluded.end_date, published=true;

