insert into public.exhibitions (id, slug, title_en, title_ro, subtitle_en, subtitle_ro, overview_en, overview_ro, start_date, end_date, venue_en, venue_ro, poster_url, published, sort_order) values ('b4a4fb7c-959c-5cfe-bba4-2ef26a17f32f', 'assignment-of-identity-receivables', 'Assignment of Identity Receivables', 'Cesiune de creanțe identitare', 'Solo show', 'Solo show', 'Although it has been grouped around a ubiquitous and personal theme (envisioning identity and its components), revolving around subjects regarding experience, memory and personal history, respectively – their transpositions into visual language, the artistic project <Assignments of identity claims> develops on two semantic complementary aspects: On the one hand, the visual (artistic) approach generating significant content involves a collection of stylistically and methodologically diverse corpora. Through them, Andreea Gabriela Tudor proposes a subjective excursion on her experiences, narratives and sources of inspiration, retrospective from the time frame in which they were made (2020-2022), but also prospective from the point of view of configuring her own artistic discourse. On the other hand, the curatorial approach aims at transferring these personal perspectives to the public, converting and assimilating them into a spectrum of immediate and unfiltered experience, phenomenon through which the identity factor (and by extension, the conceptual content) propagates and multiplies. Consequently, through the very title of the exhibition, the curatorial act presupposes the configuration of a so-called “true artistic jurisprudence”. Although the application of legal terminology to the artistic field may seem ironic (and to some extent, inappropriate), the “Brownian” diversity of current exhibition practices proves an acute need to establish set procedures and doctrines. This exhibition aims to lead by example how one can accomplish such ambitions.
